<!-- This form is for bug reports !

If you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).

If the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/.
-->



>
/kind bug



**What happened**:
Unable to spin up cluster using the kubetest, with 'ci/latest' image.
The CI jobs are failing, because the cluster is not provisioned properly.

```
I0810 23:40:23.527] Installing cfssl from vendor
I0810 23:40:23.548] Checking for custom logdump instances, if any
I0810 23:40:23.552] Sourcing kube-util.sh
I0810 23:40:23.587] Detecting project
I0810 23:40:23.588] Project: k8s-jkns-gke-reboot-1-4
I0810 23:40:23.588] Network Project: k8s-jkns-gke-reboot-1-4
I0810 23:40:23.588] Zone: us-central1-b
I0810 23:40:23.588] Dumping logs from master locally to '/workspace/_artifacts'
W0810 23:40:23.689] can't load package: package k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl: cannot find package "k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl" in any of:
W0810 23:40:23.689] 	/usr/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl (from $GOROOT)
W0810 23:40:23.690] 	/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl (from $GOPATH)
W0810 23:40:23.690] 2018/08/10 23:40:23 process.go:155: Step './hack/e2e-internal/e2e-up.sh' finished in 1m26.617131334s

```

I have tried locally, i am still getting the same error.
```
Write out database with 1 new entries
Data Base Updated
+ kube::util::ensure-cfssl /tmp/tmp.CzcIHwWJK4/cfssl
+ echo 'Installing cfssl from vendor'
Installing cfssl from vendor
+ GOBIN=
+ go install k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl
can't load package: package k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl: cannot find package "k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl" in any of:
        /usr/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl (from $GOROOT)
        /home/ubuntu/e2epath/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssl (from $GOPATH)
+ GOBIN=
+ go install k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssljson
can't load package: package k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssljson: cannot find package "k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssljson" in any of:
        /usr/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssljson (from $GOROOT)
        /home/ubuntu/e2epath/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/vendor/github.com/cloudflare/cfssl/cmd/cfssljson (from $GOPATH)
++ PATH=:/home/ubuntu/bin:/home/ubuntu/.local/bin:/home/ubuntu/y/google-cloud-sdk/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/usr/local/go/bin:/home/ubuntu/e2epath/bin:GOPATH=/home/ubuntu/e2epath
++ command -v cfssl
+ CFSSL_BIN=
++ PATH=:/home/ubuntu/bin:/home/ubuntu/.local/bin:/home/ubuntu/y/google-cloud-sdk/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/usr/local/go/bin:/home/ubuntu/e2epath/bin:GOPATH=/home/ubuntu/e2epath
++ command -v cfssljson
+ CFSSLJSON_BIN=
+ [[ ! -x '' ]]
+ echo 'Failed to install cfssl.'
Failed to install cfssl.
+ exit 1

```

[Refer PR-128](https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/poseidon/pull/128)
[Build-logs](https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/kubernetes-sigs_poseidon/128/ci-poseidon-e2e-gce/301/build-log.txt)


Could be releated to this PR #67178 


@BenTheElder @cblecker

/cc @deepak-vij
